<!--
     Schema used for the Product Configurator Start Phase posting parameters
-->
<xsd:schema elementFormDefault="qualified" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <xsd:element name="PostConfiguration">
    <xsd:annotation>
      <xsd:documentation>This is the root element.</xsd:documentation>
    </xsd:annotation>
    <xsd:complexType mixed="false">
      <xsd:sequence>
        <xsd:element name="Parameters">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>This contains parameters.</xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
          <xsd:complexType mixed="false">
            <xsd:all>
              <xsd:element name="Function" default="S" minOccurs="0">
                <xsd:annotation>
                  <xsd:documentation>This element indicates the function you wish to perform on the configuration.   The possible values are  S - Start or C - Cancel. If not supplied this element defaults to S. </xsd:documentation>
                </xsd:annotation>
                <xsd:simpleType>
                  <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
                    <xsd:whiteSpace value="preserve"/>
                    <xsd:enumeration value="S"/>
                    <xsd:enumeration value="C"/>
                  </xsd:restriction>
                </xsd:simpleType>
              </xsd:element>
              <xsd:element name="ConfigurationInstance" minOccurs="0">
                <xsd:annotation>
                  <xsd:documentation>The element indicates the instance of the configuration you are running. It is indicated by a unique number returned after the start phase of processing. This unique number is mandatory when cancelling a configuration.The size of the field is a 8 character alphanumeric field.</xsd:documentation>
                </xsd:annotation>
                <xsd:simpleType>
                  <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
                    <xsd:whiteSpace value="preserve"/>
                  </xsd:restriction>
                </xsd:simpleType>
              </xsd:element>
              <xsd:element name="IgnoreWarnings" default="N" minOccurs="0">
                <xsd:annotation>
                  <xsd:documentation>This element indicates whether or not a configuration must be rejected if there are any warnings. If not supplied it defaults to N. Valid values are N and Y.</xsd:documentation>
                </xsd:annotation>
                <xsd:simpleType>
                  <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
                    <xsd:whiteSpace value="preserve"/>
                    <xsd:enumeration value="N"/>
                    <xsd:enumeration value="Y"/>
                  </xsd:restriction>
                </xsd:simpleType>
              </xsd:element>
              <xsd:element name="ValidateWorkingDays" default="A" minOccurs="0">
                <xsd:annotation>
                  <xsd:documentation>Specifies whether to validate that the ship dates for the sales order/quote are valid working days.  If you are using an existing sales order/quote this will be ignored on the header ship date as the header ship date cannot be changed.  
When an existing sales order is not a forward order and not a scheduled order then the sales order detail lines will use the existing sales order header ship date and this element will be ignored. Possible values are: (A, ship dates will not be validated, P, ship dates will be validated and if date is not a working day, the previous valid working date will be used instead, N - ship dates will be validated and if date is not a working day, the next valid working date will be used instead). If this element is not supplied it will default to A.</xsd:documentation>
                </xsd:annotation>
                <xsd:simpleType>
                  <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
                    <xsd:whiteSpace value="preserve"/>
                    <xsd:enumeration value="A"/>
                    <xsd:enumeration value="N"/>
                    <xsd:enumeration value="P"/>
                  </xsd:restriction>
                </xsd:simpleType>
              </xsd:element>
            </xsd:all>
          </xsd:complexType>
        </xsd:element>
      </xsd:sequence>
    </xsd:complexType>
  </xsd:element>
</xsd:schema>
